  "prompt": "Is mitid valid by government?",
  "response": "MIT ID is a valid form of identification issued by the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) to its students, faculty, and staff. However, its acceptance for official government purposes can vary:\n\n1. Campus/University Use: Fully valid within MIT\n\n2. Government Identification:\n- Not typically accepted as a standalone government ID\n- Not a substitute for:\n  - Driver's license\n  - State ID\n  - Passport\n  - Government-issued photo ID\n\n3. Specific Uses:\n- May be accepted for some internal or academic verification\n- Not generally recognized for legal or official government transactions\n\nFor official government purposes, you would need a government-issued photo identification like:\n- Driver's license\n- State ID\n- Passport\n- Military ID\n\nIf you need official government identification, you should obtain the appropriate document from your state or federal government.",
